                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/943: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-24T12:00:00-04:32">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1922—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 8:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. The Minister of Foreign Affairs at a conference yesterday afternoon asked me
                    to submit to you, and through you to the President, <pb facs="0588" n="468"
                        xml:id="pg_468"/> that Bolivia considers the question which is to be
                    discussed at the conferences in Washington one in which all three participants
                    in the War of the Pacific, from which the present disputes emanated, should take
                    part; and that no lasting settlement can be effected unless all three countries
                    participate in the Washington conferences. Moreover, he states, Bolivia suffered
                    most from that war, because of the loss of her entire maritime coast, and
                    should, therefore, be given the opportunity to discuss her cause in the present
                    conference, which seems to afford an excellent opportunity to present her
                    claims.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cottrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
